On the top of the popup, the header will show.
Under the header, a text of 3 rows will be shown (all of the text will be "hard-coded").

And then three fields:

Only after he:

fields.description:
signup screen

* The signup page designs has changes
* The Sign up/sign in options are sorted as tabs \- the selected option (meaning, the page the user is standing on) wil be highlighted
* By tapping on the Sign-in option the user will navigate to the sign-in page
* *social media signup*
* the user is able to sign up with either facebook or twitter
* By tapping the "facebook" button, the user will signup with facebook and will navigate to the main page of the app
* By tapping the "twitter" button, the user will signup with twitter and will navigate to the main page of the app
* *regular signup*
* The user is able to sign up using \- full name, email and a password
* 4 text fields will appear
* By tapping a certain field a native keyboard will appear
* all 4 fields are required \- if the user didn't fill them properly and tapped the sign-up button he will see an indication "required" and won't be able to proceed
* The full name field is a letter only field
* The confirm password field has to match to the password field \- otherwise, the user won't be able to procced and he will see an indication
* *more info*
* under the regular signup fields will be a text. "more info" will act as a clickable link
* by tapping the "more info" link the user will navigate to the Welcome screen
* *signup button*
* By tapping the signup button the user will be able to sign-up and will navigate to the main page of the app
* the user won't be able to continue by tapping the signup button unless all field are filled correctly and unless password field and confirm password fields are identical
* *terms of use and privacy policy*
* beneath the signup button will appear a text
* the text will include a link to the privacy policy of the app and a link to the terms of use of the app

Clicking on a group that all ready in red, will cancel the red mark and bring the group to be enable again on the "add food" suction.
Clicking on a header (Category) will act the same as clicking on a group, but will effect all of his groups.
If a category are mark in red (and all of his groups) and the user are clicking  on a red group
Switching between the tabs wont delete the changes.
